HEADWORD: Forcemeat
<hw>Force"meat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupt. for
<ets>farce-meat</ets>, fr. F. <ets>farce</ets> stuffing. See
<er>Farce</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>Meat
chopped fine and highly seasoned, either served up alone, or used as a
stuffing.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>forced
meat</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

